-- Mexico Stocks: Empresas Ica, Modelo, TV Azteca, Televisa Drop
-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 2012-01-13T20:22:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-13/mexico-stocks-empresas-ica-modelo-tv-azteca-televisa-drop.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 2:02 p.m. local time.  The IPC  index  fell 2.2 percent to 36,499.22.  Mexican stocks followed global equities lower as  France  was
stripped of its top  credit rating  by  Standard & Poor’s .  Grupo Modelo SA (GMODELOC)  , Mexico’s largest beer maker,
fell 3.9 percent to 84.03 pesos.  TV Azteca SAB (TVAZTCPO)  ,
Mexico’s second-largest broadcast television network, declined
2.6 percent to 8.78 pesos.  Empresas Ica SAB (ICA*)  , the
country’s biggest construction company, fell 3.7 percent to
17.39 pesos.  Grupo Televisa SA (TLEVICPO)  , the world’s largest
Spanish-language broadcaster, fell 3.8 percent to 56.26 pesos.
Grupo Financiero BBVA Bancomer SA assigned a rating of
“underperform” to the shares.  To contact the reporter on this story:
